title: JUI candidate Akram Khan Durrani wins PK-102
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamiat Ullema-e-Islam candidate Akram Khan Durrani won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-102 Bannu-IV by securing 39,061 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Malik Adnan Khan who bagged 35,825 votes.
Votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 42.74 per cent.
